{
  "name": "@mjfuertesf/pi-dumb-meter",
  "latest_version": "0.1.1",
  "description": "Context-pressure footer meter extension for Pi",
  "readme": "# pi-dumb-meter\n\nContext-pressure footer meter extension for Pi.\n\n`pi-dumb-meter` shows a compact token/context usage meter in Pi's footer and can warn when the current session reaches your configured limit.\n\n## Install\n\n```bash\npi install git:gitlab.com/mjfuertesf/pi-dumb-meter\npi install npm:@mjfuertesf/pi-dumb-meter\n```\n\nRepo: https://gitlab.com/mjfuertesf/pi-dumb-meter\n\n## Demo\n\n### Footer meter\n\n![pi-dumb-meter demo 1](./assets/screenshots/pi-dumb-meter-demo-1.png)\n\n### Commands\n\n![pi-dumb-meter demo 2](./assets/screenshots/pi-dumb-meter-demo-2.png)\n\n### Over-limit state\n\n![pi-dumb-meter demo 3](./assets/screenshots/pi-dumb-meter-demo-3.png)\n\n## Usage\n\n`pi-dumb-meter` publishes the `dumb-meter` footer status and reads config from `~/.pi/agent/settings.json`.\n\nCommands:\n\n```text\n/dumb-meter-limit [tokens|percent]\n/dumb-meter-label [on|off]\n/dumb-meter-full [on|off]\n```\n\nExamples:\n\n```text\n/dumb-meter-limit 80%\n/dumb-meter-limit 120k\n/dumb-meter-label off\n/dumb-meter-full off\n```\n\n## Development\n\n```bash\nnpm install\nnpm test\n```\n\n`npm test` runs:\n\n```bash\ntsx --test ./*.test.ts\n```\n",
  "keywords": [
